# SPECIEST Reading Companion — Vercel Deployment

## Project structure

```
speciest-companion/
├── api/
│   └── chat.js        ← Serverless proxy (keeps your API key private)
├── public/
│   └── index.html     ← The reading companion app
├── vercel.json        ← Vercel routing config
└── .env.example       ← Shows which env variable to set
```

---

## Deploy in 5 steps

### 1. Create a GitHub repo
- Go to github.com → New repository → name it `speciest-companion`
- Upload this entire folder

### 2. Import into Vercel
- Go to vercel.com → Add New Project
- Import your `speciest-companion` GitHub repo
- Framework preset: **Other**
- Click Deploy (it will fail the first time — that's OK, no API key yet)

### 3. Add your API key
- In Vercel dashboard → your project → **Settings → Environment Variables**
- Add:
  - Name: `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`
  - Value: `sk-ant-...` (your key from console.anthropic.com)
  - Environment: Production ✓, Preview ✓
- Click Save

### 4. Redeploy
- Vercel dashboard → Deployments → click the three dots → **Redeploy**
- Your app will be live at `https://speciest-companion.vercel.app`

### 5. Set your custom subdomain (optional but recommended)
- Vercel → Settings → Domains → add `companion.lisapedrosa.com`
- In Crazy Domains, add a CNAME record:
  - Name: `companion`
  - Value: `cname.vercel-dns.com`

---

## Add to lisapedrosa.com (WordPress/Elementor)

Add this to any page using an HTML widget:

```html
<iframe 
  src="https://companion.lisapedrosa.com" 
  width="100%" 
  height="900px" 
  frameborder="0"
  style="border:none;">
</iframe>
```

Or link to it directly from your nav menu as a new page.

---

## Update allowed origins

Once your Vercel URL is confirmed, open `api/chat.js` and update:

```js
const ALLOWED_ORIGINS = [
  'https://lisapedrosa.com',
  'https://www.lisapedrosa.com',
  'https://speciest-companion.vercel.app',  // ← your actual URL
];
```

---

## Rate limits

The proxy allows 20 requests per IP per minute by default.
Adjust in `api/chat.js` — change `RATE_LIMIT` and `RATE_WINDOW`.
